==ᱦᱚᱲ ᱠᱚ==
'''ᱨᱤᱱᱰᱚ ᱢᱟᱡᱷᱤᱺ''' ᱚᱥᱥᱟ ᱨᱤᱱᱤᱡ ᱯᱷᱨᱤᱰᱚᱢ ᱯᱷᱟᱤᱴᱚᱨ, ᱩᱱᱤ ᱫᱚ ᱵᱨᱤᱡ ᱨᱟᱡ ᱵᱤᱨᱩᱫ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱷᱚᱱᱰᱟ ᱨᱤᱵᱷᱚᱞᱩᱥᱚᱱ ᱮ ᱟᱜᱩ ᱞᱮᱟᱭ ᱾<ref name="ReferenceA">D.K. Joshi, S. Mund, M.P.Mishra, The Kandha Revolution in Kalahandi, Orissa Review, Aug 2007</ref>

'''ᱵᱷᱩᱵᱟ.ᱱᱮᱥᱣᱟ.ᱨ ᱵᱮᱷᱮᱨᱟᱺ''' ᱮᱸᱡᱤᱸᱤᱭᱚᱨ, ᱮᱠᱟᱰᱮᱢᱤᱠ, ᱮᱰᱢᱤᱸᱤᱥᱴᱨᱮᱴᱚᱨᱥ ᱟᱨ ᱞᱮᱠᱦᱚᱠ ᱾<ref>{{cite web|author=Sambit Misra |url=http://www.odiya.org/personality/perslink/bbehera.html |title=Professor Bhubaneswar Behera |publisher=Odiya.org |date=2001-04-25 |accessdate=2013-05-22}}</ref>

'''ᱨᱟᱢ ᱪᱚᱸᱰᱨᱟᱢᱨᱚ ᱯᱟᱨᱚ, ᱟᱤ . ᱮ . ᱮᱥ ᱺ''' (᱑᱙᱑᱙ᱼ᱒᱐᱑᱓) ᱵᱤᱭᱩᱨᱚᱠᱨᱟᱯᱴ, ᱥᱚᱥᱤᱭᱟᱞ ᱣᱟᱨᱠᱚᱨ, ᱟᱨ ᱮᱰᱢᱤᱱᱤᱥᱴᱨᱮᱴᱚᱨ ᱾<ref>Samabad, 2000</ref><ref>Keun Mahatabanak Pain, Gana nath Das, The Prajatantra, 2 January 1988</ref>  

'''ᱯᱨᱚᱯᱷᱩᱞᱞᱚ ᱨᱚᱛᱷᱚᱺ''' ᱱᱚᱛᱭᱚᱨᱟ.ᱥᱢᱤ ᱛᱮ ᱠᱚ ᱥᱚᱢᱢᱟᱱᱤᱛ ᱞᱮᱫᱮᱭᱟᱠᱚ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱚᱰᱤᱭᱟ ᱰᱨᱟᱞ ᱚᱞ ᱞᱟᱜᱤᱫ ᱛᱮ ᱾<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.airbpn.org/about.htm |title=Akashvani, Bhawanipatna - Home |publisher=Airbpn.org |date= |accessdate=2013-05-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120802091308/http://www.airbpn.org/about.htm |archivedate=2012-08-02 |df= }}</ref>

'''ᱫᱚᱭᱟᱱᱤᱫᱷᱤ ᱱᱟᱭᱚᱠᱺ''' ᱠᱚᱞᱟᱷᱟᱱᱰᱤ ᱤᱡ ᱫᱚᱞᱤᱛ ᱞᱤᱰᱚᱨ ᱟᱨ ᱢᱟᱲᱟᱝ ᱤᱡ ᱢᱚᱱᱛᱨᱤ ᱾<ref>Kalahandi Express, Sept 2010</ref>

'''ᱠᱤᱥᱟᱱ ᱯᱟᱴᱱᱟᱭᱟᱠᱺ''' ᱥᱚᱢᱟᱡ ᱥᱮᱵᱤ ᱾<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cpiml.org/liberation/year_2004/November/obituary.htm |title=Obituary |publisher=Cpiml.org |date=2004-10-08 |accessdate=2013-05-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525002428/http://www.cpiml.org/liberation/year_2004/November/obituary.htm |archivedate=2013-05-25 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://archive.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/sep272004/update2.asp |title=Socialist leader Kishan Patnaik dead - Deccan Herald |publisher=Archive.deccanherald.com |date=2004-09-27 |accessdate=2013-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925050906/http://archive.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/sep272004/update2.asp |archive-date=25 September 2015 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hindu.com/2004/09/30/stories/2004093001380300.htm | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title=Kishan Patnaik remembered | date=30 September 2004}}</ref>
